{
  "texts": [
    "Next, we turn our attention to the representation of concepts instead of examples.",
    "Our model predicts that single neurons exhibit more concept information per spike during dense activity regimes (Fig. 6A).",
    "To test this prediction using the same CRCNS hc-3 dataset, we invoke the aforementioned equivalence between concepts in our model and coarser positions along a linear track (Fig. 6B).",
    "Thus, single CA3 neurons should encode more information per spike about coarse positions during dense theta phases.",
    "Previously, to test for finer position encoding in Fig. 5, we divided single place fields into multiple position bins during the computation of information."
  ]
}